 <h2 id="01">BackupFilePath</h2>

 <p>Backup <i>FilePath</i> to a SQLite database file and access later.</p>

 <p>It could be regarded as a simple versioning system as it is similar,
 though a backup system was chosen to imply that is not to replace a
 proper versioning system. It is probably something in between as it
 is not to replace a proper dedicated backup system either.
 As it is full content backup, it could also be used to store
 different variations of a file.</p>

 <p>A versioning system is incremental differencing, while this is
 full content backup. It can be used within a directory based version
 system like Git without conflict. It can do this as it is only for the
 target file. It is suitable for temporary backups or can be long term
 use like a versioning system. The later is inefficient based on the
 size increase of the database and might be better instead with a
 proper versioning system.</p>

 <p>The database name will be like <code>filename.ext.backups</code>
 if the target file is named <code>filename.ext</code>.</p>

 <p>Modes:</p>

 <dl>
  <dt>Commit filepath</dt>
  <dd>Read <i>FilePath</i> and insert into the database.
  The full content is saved as a type blob.</dd>

  <dt>Delete any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to delete that commit.
  A vacuum operation will occur to reduce the size of the database.</dd>

  <dt>Edit the database</dt>
  <dd>Edit the database with an installed DB Browser for SQLite.</dd>

  <dt>Open any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to open a new tab and insert the content
  into the editor pane.</dd>

  <dt>Print all comments</dt>
  <dd>Print all comments from the database to the output pane.</dd>

  <dt>Restore any commit to edit pane</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to clear the content and then insert the
  content from the commit into the editor pane.</dd>

  <dt>Restore any commit to filepath</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to write the content to <i>FilePath</i>.</dd>

  <dt>WinMerge any commit</dt>
  <dd>Select any commit to write to a temporary file and compare
  with <i>FilePath</i> in WinMerge.</dd>
 </dl>



 <h2 id="02">ClearAll</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations and marks.</p>



 <h2 id="03">ClearAnnotations</h2>

 <p>Clear all annotations.</p>



 <h2 id="04">ClearBookmarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all bookmarks.</p>

 <p>Does same action as <i>Search -> Clear All Bookmarks</i>
 from the SciTE editor menu.</p>



 <h2 id="05">ClearErrormarks</h2>

 <p>Clear all error marks created by double click on red error lines in the
 output pane.</p>



 <h2 id="06">ClearOthermarks</h2>

 <p>Clear marks that programs may add.</p>

 <p>The user may not see these marks unless were added by a
 custom script or program.</p>



 <h2 id="07">CopyFileDir</h2>

 <p>Copy file directory path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="08">CopyFileName</h2>

 <p>Copy filename without extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="09">CopyFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Copy filename with extension to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="10">CopyFilePath</h2>

 <p>Copy absolute file path to the clipboard.</p>



 <h2 id="11">CurSelCountBraces</h2>

 <p>Count braces in current selection. Prints the result to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Braces:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>( )</li>
  <li>{ }</li>
  <li>[ ]</li>
  <li>&lt; &gt;</li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="12">DiffFileNameExt</h2>

 <p>Diff <i>FileNameExt</i> with fossil or git.</p>



 <h2 id="13">EskilFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Eskil to diff <i>FilePath</i> with a checkout</p>

 <p>Eskil expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciTEDefaultHome)\eskil\eskil.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="14">FrhedFilePath</h2>

 <p>Run Frhed to hex edit <i>FilePath</i>.</p>

 <p>Frhed expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"$(SciTEDefaultHome)\frhed\frhed.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="15">InsertDate</h2>

 <p>Insert date at position of caret.</p>

 <p>If <code>yyyy-mm-dd</code> pattern with digits is selected,
 the selection will be replaced with current date.</p>



 <h2 id="16">OpenAbbrevFile</h2>

 <p>Open a <i>abbrev.properties</i> file which is searched
 in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="17">OpenApiFile</h2>

 <p>Open a api file which is searched in
 <code>"$(SciteDefaultHome)\api"</code>.</p>



 <h2 id="18">OpenChmFile</h2>

 <p>Open a chm file which is searched in the subfolders of
 <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>

 <p>Some other locations may be searched, example <i>scite.chm</i>
 in the root of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="19">OpenFileDir</h2>

 <p>Open the file directory in a file browser like explorer.</p>



 <h2 id="20">OpenHtaFile</h2>

 <p>Open a hta file which is searched in the subfolders
 of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="21">OpenLuaExtensionFile</h2>

 <p>Open a lua extension file which is searched as <i>extension.lua</i>
 in the subfolders of <i>SciteDefaultHome</i>.</p>



 <h2 id="22">OpenSciteVarsFile</h2>

 <p>Open <i>scitevars.cfg</i> file which can be used by PrintSciteVars.</p>



 <h2 id="23">PrintApiKeywords</h2>

 <p>Print keywords from api files, like those used in autocomplete.</p>



 <h2 id="24">PrintApiLuaPropFiles</h2>

 <p>Print api, lua and properties files.</p>



 <h2 id="25">PrintAsciiTable</h2>

 <p>Print an ASCII table to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Includes Extended ASCII. May need to have the codepage
 set to 0 to show the Extended ASCII correct.</p>



 <h2 id="26">PrintCommentLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Filetypes supported:</p>

 <ul>
  <li>au3</li>
  <li>cmd</li>
  <li>lua</li>
  <li>pas</li>
  <li>php</li>
  <li>properties</li>
  <li>ps1</li>
  <li>py</li>
 </ul>



 <h2 id="27">PrintCommentedCodeLines</h2>

 <p>Get comment code lines from the editor pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Same filetypes supported as PrintCommentLines.</p>



 <h2 id="28">PrintFindText</h2>

 <p>Print search results found from selected text or current word.</p>

 <p>Like the find and search built into SciTE, except this can print the
 results to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Based on code from <i>http://lua-users.org/wiki/SciteMiscScripts</i></p>



 <h2 id="29">PrintGlobalNames... PrintGlobalTables...</h2>

 <p>Print Lua names and tables.</p>

 <p>Used for viewing and debugging the Lua internals which is why it is
 included as a extended tool for use as it is for special use.</p>



 <h2 id="30">PrintReminders</h2>

 <p>Find reminder lines in the edit pane and print to the output pane.</p>

 <p>Currently searches for these words with a trailing colon:</p>

 <ul>
  <li><code>debug:</code></li>
  <li><code>reminder:</code></li>
  <li><code>test:</code></li>
  <li><code>testing:</code></li>
  <li><code>todo:</code></li>
 </ul>

 <p>Based on code from RSciTE.</p>



 <h2 id="31">PrintSciteVars</h2>

 <p>Print SciTE property variables.</p>

 <p>By default, prints the standard variables defined in <i>SciTEDoc.html</i>.
 If <i>scitevars.cfg</i> is located in <i>SciTEDefaultHome</i>, the file will
 be read for property variable names and will include them. Comment lines
 starting with <code>;</code> or <code>#</code> will be ignored when the
 file is read.</p>



 <h2 id="32">ReplaceSelEscape</h2>

 <p>Escapes certain special characters used in some languages.</p>

 <p>Currently does api, bat, cmd, hta, html, lua, py, pyw, sql.</p>

 <p>Escaping in general is very broad, though an example is for html:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>&amp;amp;</pre></code>



 <h2 id="33">ReplaceSelSortLines</h2>

 <p>Sorts a selection of text by line.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>item3
item1
item2</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>item1
item2
item3</pre></code>



 <h2 id="34">ReplaceSelSortList</h2>

 <p>Sorts a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item3", "item1", "item2"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="35">ReplaceSelWrapList</h2>

 <p>Wraps a JSON style list.</p>

 <p>Example:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1", "item2", "item3"]</pre></code>

 <p>changes to:</p>

 <code><pre>["item1",
 "item2",
 "item3"]</pre></code>



 <h2 id="36">SelectCalltipColour</h2>

 <p>Change colours of both autocomplete and calltip popups.</p>



 <h2 id="37">StartExeFile</h2>

 <p>Run executables in the subfolders of <code>SciteDefaultHome</code>.</p>

 <p>Executables can be added to subfolders, such as Frhed.
 StartExeFile will run these executables without any arguments.</p>



 <h2 id="38">StripTrailingSpaces</h2>

 <p>Strip trailing spaces from the current document in the edit pane.</p>

 <p>SciTE can be set to strip whitespace characters at end of lines.
 This tool allows the user to strip the end of lines in the edit pane.
 Can be useful if the property of <i>strip.trailing.spaces</i> is not
 used globally or by the current filepattern.</p>



 <h2 id="39">ToggleCodePage</h2>

 <p>Toggle between 0 (ANSI), 65001 (UTF8) and the actual codepage.</p>



 <h2 id="40">ToggleDimComments</h2>

 <p>Toggle comment colours from normal colour to a lighter colour.</p>

 <p>Dimming may not be useful for general programming though debugging
 code with dimmed comments may help with focus. Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="41">ToggleExtendedTools</h2>

 <p>Toggle the ListBox to show or hide the extended tools.</p>

 <p>Initially, some tools may not be shown in the ListBox, due to not being
 suitable for regular use. This option allows the user to toggle the list by
 reshowing the ListBox with or without the extended tools. Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="42">ToggleHighlightCurrentWord</h2>

 <p>Toggle highlight current word at position of the caret.</p>

 <p>For distraction free programming, default to off.
 Toggles on or off.</p>



 <h2 id="43">ToggleMonospaceFont</h2>

 <p>Toggle with monospace font and proportional font.</p>

 <p>If <i>font.override</i> property has been appended to
 global font properties, default font is monospace.
 This function allows proportional font.</p>



 <h2 id="44">WinMergeFilePath</h2>

 <p>Passes <i>FilePath</i> as 1st argument to WinMerge.
 WinMerge will then show the <i>Select Files or Folders dialog</i>.
 Choose your settings and then press the <i>Compare</i> button.</p>

 <p>WinMerge expected location:&nbsp;
 <code>"%ProgramFiles%\WinMerge\WinMergeU.exe"</code></p>



 <h2 id="45">WinMergeFilePath unsaved</h2>

 <p>Compares the edit pane content with <i>FilePath</i> content.</p>

 <p>The edit pane of SciTE is read and saved to a temporary file
 and is passed as the 1st file argument to WinMerge.
 The <i>FilePath</i> is passed as the 2nd file argument to WinMerge.</p>

 <p>This can be useful if you do not know the difference between the
 edit pane content and the file content. Especially if a messagebox asks
 to reload from file to determine whether to save or not after the reload.
 If the later is the case, select <i>No</i> to the messagebox and then use
 this tool to compare. <i>File -> Revert</i> menu item can be used if
 <i>FilePath</i> on disk is wanted after the compare is done.</p>

